This paper is about generating novel actions for a humanoid robot using a dynamic neural network model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses machine learning and neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the self-organization of the memory structure, which is a characteristic of neural networks, indicating that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper is about human-robot interaction, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
